        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Unto the house which he had built — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "This house he had built for her, because the ark was now in the house of David, which therefore ought to be kept pure and free from every danger and appearance of pollution. For though Pharaoh’s daughter was proselyted to the Jewish religion, and had renounced idolatry, it is not likely that both she and all her servants had embraced the whole law of Moses; and therefore they might many ways defile a place made sacred by that symbol of the divine presence.",
